# <type>(<optional scope>): <short summary>   ← 50 chars or less
#
# <optional body: explain *what* and *why*, wrap at ~72 chars>
#
# <optional footer: BREAKING CHANGE: ... | Refs: #123 | Closes: #123>
#
# --- Conventional Commits cheat sheet --------------------------------
# Allowed types:
#   feat     A new feature
#   fix      A bug fix
#   docs     Documentation only changes
#   style    Formatting; no code-meaning changes
#   refactor Code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
#   perf     A change that improves performance
#   test     Adding or correcting tests
#   build    Build system or external dependency changes
#   ci       CI configuration files and scripts
#   chore    Other changes that don't modify src or test files
#   revert   Reverts a previous commit
#
# Breaking changes: append "!" after type/scope OR add a
# "BREAKING CHANGE:" footer.
#   e.g.  feat(api)!: drop support for legacy endpoint
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
